It is possible, but it's clunky. You have to put your files in a RAR archive, append it to a PNG (JPG files don't work), and then upload it. To do it in reverse, download the image, change the extension to RAR, and open it in WinRar (doesn't work in 7zip). See >>/suggest/4186.
Tomorrow I'll try making a tool that automates most of this process, and doesn't force you to use a RAR archive.
